<h2>Poster Image Tips</h2>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Use a representative frame</strong> that accurately reflects the video content. Avoid generic thumbnails.</li>
  <li><strong>Optimize the poster image</strong> with WebP or AVIF format and appropriate compression. A 200KB poster defeats the purpose of <code>preload="none"</code>.</li>
  <li><strong>Add a play button overlay</strong> in the poster image if the native controls do not make it obvious the element is a video.</li>
  <li><strong>Generate posters at the video's intrinsic resolution.</strong> The browser scales the image to fill the video element.</li>
</ul>

